The paper focuses on detecting refactoring opportunities in software programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The approach involves measuring the participation of references between types, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD) sub-categories. The validation of the technique is done using an experiment, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the detected refactorings, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
